name: UDUPI Pure Veg Restaurant

reviews.review_text: Regular Udupi restaurant. Food quality is good. Service is excellent. We had Veg Hyderabadi with Chapati and Butter milk it was delicious. Masala papad was tasty.

Food was very good. Service was quick. The staff was kind. You will get the taste of the south.
The food items like varieties of halwa, laddo available at the billing counter were also good.

Udapi Pure Veg: A Taste of Tradition
Nestled along the bustling Panji Ponda Road, Udapi Pure Veg is a culinary gem that transports you to the heart of South Indian cuisine. This unassuming eatery offers a simple yet satisfying menu that is sure to leave you craving more.

The moment you step inside, you're greeted by a warm and inviting atmosphere. The aroma of freshly ground spices fills the air, setting the stage for a delightful dining experience. The menu is a treasure trove of classic South Indian dishes, from fluffy idlis and crispy dosas to aromatic curries and flavorful biryanis.
I was particularly impressed by the masala dosa. The crepe was thin and crispy, filled with a flavorful potato masala that was perfectly spiced. The accompanying sambar and coconut chutney complemented the dosa beautifully. For those with a sweet tooth, the kesari bath is a must-try. This sweet vermicelli pudding is rich, creamy, and bursting with flavor.

The service at Udapi Pure Veg is efficient and friendly. The staff is always happy to recommend dishes or answer any questions. While the restaurant may not be the fanciest place in town, the quality of the food and the warm hospitality make it a truly special dining experience.

If you're looking for a taste of authentic South Indian cuisine in Old Goa, Udapi Pure Veg is a must-visit. The simple yet delicious food, warm atmosphere, and friendly service make it a hidden gem that is well worth seeking out.
I highly recommend Udapi Pure Veg to anyone looking for a delicious and affordable meal. It's a place that I will definitely be returning to in the future.

* Price:
Udapi Pure Veg is very affordable. You can expect to pay around ₹200-300 for a meal for two.

* Ambience:
The restaurant is simple and unpretentious. It's a good place to enjoy a casual meal with friends or family.

* Service:
The service at Udapi Pure Veg is efficient and friendly. The staff is always happy to help.

* Location:
The restaurant is located on Panji Ponda Road, near the Old Goa Church.

* Timings:
The restaurant is open from 7 am to 10:30 pm every day.
Overall, I had a fantastic experience at Udapi Pure Veg. It's a great place to enjoy delicious South Indian food in a relaxed and friendly atmosphere. I highly recommend this restaurant to anyone visiting Old Goa.

description:
**Udupi Pure Veg Restaurant: A Slice of South Indian Tradition in Corlim**

Tucked away in the bustling Corlim Industrial Estate, Udupi Pure Veg Restaurant charms visitors with its inviting atmosphere and authentic Udupi cuisine. With a commendable rating of 3.8 out of 5 from over 2,600 reviews, this eatery enjoys a solid reputation among both locals and tourists alike. Frequent tags highlight its specialties, with ‘thali’ (25 mentions), ‘snacks’ (21 mentions), ‘highway’ (11 mentions), and ‘udupi cuisine’ (10 mentions) suggesting that the restaurant is best known for its traditional offerings and convenient location.

**Ambiance & Design**

As you enter Udupi Pure Veg, the warmth of its ambiance envelopes you, inviting you into a world where tradition and simplicity reign. The decor is unpretentious yet welcoming, making it an ideal spot for casual dining with family or friends. The lighting is soft, enhancing the cozy atmosphere, while the faint scent of freshly prepared spices wafts through the air, beckoning your appetite. Customers have noted the charm of this establishment in their reviews, praising its relaxed vibe that perfectly complements the laid-back dining experience.

![Udupi Pure Veg Atmosphere](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/geougc-cs/AHRlGdmVfg63RRBKNv3aK2q_M2T1D4GUDs9NVzdz6xON-cSkl1Iu5lr2otOttcWiv0evDy_q_0iuSIUVYlbT0lC2LiVNKvIR3yPRuweMFb52IsU92VC1mxOojIvfSHmX73kbVJkBFiYj=w375-h281-p)

**Menu & Culinary Experience**

The menu at Udupi Pure Veg is a delightful journey through South Indian cuisine, featuring a plethora of vegetarian dishes that cater to all tastes and cravings. Signature dishes such as the masala dosa—a thin, crispy crepe filled with a perfectly spiced potato mixture—stand out among the options. Reviewers highlight the accompanying coconut chutney and sambar, which elevate the experience even further. The restaurant also boasts an impressive variety of thalis, providing a complete culinary experience on a single platter. 

For those with a sweet tooth, be sure to try the kesari bath, a rich and creamy sweet vermicelli pudding that leaves a lasting impression. Reviewers have appreciated the affordability of the meals, with prices generally hovering around ₹200-300 for two people, making it accessible for all.

![Delicious South Indian Thali](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/geougc-cs/AHRlGdkbhgKNkmyYNJAzaBl-iDe2usDdZ4FH4FUQmz0uBAKhEQaf9DtRY4GwKEc4Zsm-HX5H-S6Dx2vg7OeyEqkwuY85Q3RWzU5nGQ78TZtOy0-Ym-ld0qmVd2tlUm-PXF5t4qYFapmk=w375-h281-p)

**Customer Experience & Service**

Service at Udupi Pure Veg receives consistent praise for being friendly and efficient. Many reviews highlight the hospitality of the staff, who are eager to suggest dishes and ensure a pleasant dining experience. The restaurant offers both walk-in and reservation options, making it convenient for those looking to enjoy a quick meal on the go. One satisfied customer noted, “The service was quick, and the staff was kind,” emphasizing the attentive nature of the team.

![Udupi Restaurant Staff](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/geougc-cs/AHRlGdnFbGj1XU92Z_9MFvOqumV6OzY5andSlg7YRuXu6miVDqapCFH_5CR4Dt_9oMO-sLjhpF3fTTTUyYXu7K15OjzYdx6NRf9Bj4JCbQJczPGOi6H_rCe7tWD0CFmflV1ej6MttlAo=w375-h281-p)

**Popularity & Reviews**

Udupi Pure Veg has cultivated a loyal following, with many customers returning for its comforting South Indian flavors. The restaurant's social media presence reflects its popularity, with numerous positive reviews underscoring that it's a staple for anyone looking to indulge in authentic Udupi cuisine. Though it might not have received any specific awards, the buzz among diners is a testament to its quality and reliability.

Overall, Udupi Pure Veg Restaurant promises a delightful dining experience steeped in tradition and flavor. Whether you're stopping in for a quick snack or enjoying a leisurely meal, this hidden gem is sure to satisfy your cravings for delicious South Indian fare. With its warm atmosphere, friendly service, and mouth-watering menu, it remains a must-visit eatery for locals and travelers alike.
